1
00:01:16,410 --> 00:01:17,953
This will make you happy.

2
00:01:18,537 --> 00:01:19,914
I'll only be getting

3
00:01:19,997 --> 00:01:22,374
half of what you get paid.

4
00:01:25,169 --> 00:01:27,338
You said you'd do it
for double my pay, remember?

5
00:01:37,973 --> 00:01:38,808
Let's go.

6
00:01:43,395 --> 00:01:44,688
Hello.

7
00:01:44,772 --> 00:01:48,150
I'm Gwon Se-na, and I'll be joining
the cast of Good Detective Kang Pil-gu.

8
00:01:48,234 --> 00:01:49,109
Wow!

9
00:01:58,702 --> 00:02:00,913
About that video I handed over to you…

10
00:02:00,996 --> 00:02:03,916
There was one more person
who wasn't in it.

11
00:02:03,999 --> 00:02:05,960
Someone really famous.

12
00:02:06,669 --> 00:02:07,920
Gwon Se-na.

13
00:02:11,590 --> 00:02:15,219
I'm just too scared
to keep this to myself.

14
00:02:21,517 --> 00:02:24,812
POSSIBLE 3RD-PARTY INVOLVEMENT?

15
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:46,375
Bro, are you okay?

16
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,252
What's wrong? Can you not breathe again?

17
00:02:48,836 --> 00:02:51,046
-Try exhaling.
-It's not that.

18
00:02:51,130 --> 00:02:52,131
Breathe! Come on!

19
00:02:52,214 --> 00:02:53,883
I said it's not that!

20
00:02:53,966 --> 00:02:55,885
It's not that I can't breathe.

21
00:02:56,468 --> 00:03:00,931
I'm just too pissed off to breathe!

22
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:05,895
I only just found out about Se-na myself.

23
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:07,855
You really didn't know?

24
00:03:07,938 --> 00:03:09,481
I swear, I didn't know!

25
00:03:09,565 --> 00:03:13,694
-Why would I risk it and lie to you?
-How the hell could you not know?

26
00:03:13,777 --> 00:03:16,030
I guess since we turned down the movie,

27
00:03:16,113 --> 00:03:18,073
they kept it a secret
so it wouldn't fall through again.

28
00:03:18,157 --> 00:03:19,950
Stop lying!

29
00:03:20,034 --> 00:03:21,994
Okay, listen to me, bro.

30
00:03:34,006 --> 00:03:34,924
I'm sorry.

31
00:03:37,009 --> 00:03:38,844
But I can't film the drama

32
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:41,597
with Ms. Gwon Se-na.

33
00:03:42,806 --> 00:03:44,391
I like Mr. Lim Hyeon-jun.

34
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,191
You know we used to date, right?

35
00:03:54,318 --> 00:03:55,611
You didn't know?

36
00:03:55,694 --> 00:03:56,862
Am I the only one who didn't know?

37
00:03:57,404 --> 00:04:00,240
I was awful to him when we broke up,

38
00:04:00,324 --> 00:04:01,867
so Hyeon-jun is very angry with me.

39
00:04:01,951 --> 00:04:04,662
I want to use this as an opportunity
to make up with him.

40
00:04:05,663 --> 00:04:06,914
You'll help me, right?

41
00:04:21,136 --> 00:04:23,931
In the story, Ju-ri and Hun-seok
meet through a dating app.

42
00:04:24,014 --> 00:04:26,558
Have you used one before?

43
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:30,646
Do girls really meet guys
through dating apps?

44
00:04:30,729 --> 00:04:32,231
Isn't that what f****** losers do?

45
00:04:33,899 --> 00:04:35,359
I'm so f****** exhausted.

46
00:04:36,235 --> 00:04:37,945
Hey, can you pass me that?

47
00:04:46,912 --> 00:04:48,330
I'm sorry, everyone.

48
00:04:48,914 --> 00:04:50,791
I'm still hungover, you see.

49
00:04:50,874 --> 00:04:52,334
Don't be mad at me!

50
00:05:02,594 --> 00:05:03,595
I'm so f****** tired.

51
00:05:07,683 --> 00:05:08,892
I'm so sorry.

52
00:05:08,976 --> 00:05:10,936
I worked late last night
and didn't get any sleep.

53
00:05:11,020 --> 00:05:13,022
I'm sorry.

54
00:05:13,105 --> 00:05:14,189
Don't be mad at me!

55
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:17,067
By the way,

56
00:05:17,151 --> 00:05:19,945
-can I get one of those too?
-What?

57
00:05:20,029 --> 00:05:21,572
This interview is so boring

58
00:05:22,156 --> 00:05:24,074
that I need one of those to wake up.

59
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:30,039
I'm so sorry!

60
00:05:31,206 --> 00:05:32,458
Hey, hand me my phone.

61
00:05:40,466 --> 00:05:41,508
I'm glad that's off my chest.

62
00:05:44,094 --> 00:05:44,970
You want to make up?

63
00:05:45,554 --> 00:05:46,638
You and me?

64
00:05:47,681 --> 00:05:50,225
What made you even think of
being in this drama?

65
00:05:50,309 --> 00:05:51,894
I knew you'd never drop Kang Pil-gu.

66
00:05:51,977 --> 00:05:52,936
Then what about that movie?

67
00:05:53,020 --> 00:05:55,564
I turned it down after you did.

68
00:05:56,648 --> 00:05:58,358
Is that so? Yay for me!

69
00:05:58,442 --> 00:06:01,070
Then I'll drop Kang Pil-gu
and do that movie instead.

70
00:06:01,153 --> 00:06:02,905
Then I'll do that movie too.

71
00:06:05,032 --> 00:06:06,283
What are you up to?

72
00:06:06,867 --> 00:06:08,035
I told you.

73
00:06:08,118 --> 00:06:10,788
I still have feelings for you
and want to make up.

74
00:06:13,248 --> 00:06:14,666
Gwon Se-na, snap out of it.

75
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,836
How can we possibly work together
on the same project?

76
00:06:18,712 --> 00:06:20,589
We can't possibly work together
on the same project.

77
00:06:21,173 --> 00:06:23,092
I really need this role.

78
00:06:24,051 --> 00:06:26,470
Do you want me to disappear entirely
from this industry?

79
00:06:29,056 --> 00:06:30,432
Yes.

80
00:06:30,516 --> 00:06:31,892
It'd be great if you disappeared.

81
00:06:33,018 --> 00:06:34,186
I was horrible, wasn't I?

82
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:35,562
I was too young to know better.

83
00:06:35,646 --> 00:06:36,730
Don't make excuses.

84
00:06:37,731 --> 00:06:40,192
I was young too,
and I was desperate for that role.

85
00:06:41,985 --> 00:06:45,948
I don't want to apologize
or ask for your forgiveness.

86
00:06:46,031 --> 00:06:48,492
I stopped making
pathetic excuses like that ages ago,

87
00:06:48,575 --> 00:06:49,827
so I can't even say it.

88
00:06:50,619 --> 00:06:53,080
Can't you just think of it this way?

89
00:06:54,081 --> 00:06:55,791
Let's pretend we're meeting
for the first time today.

90
00:06:56,667 --> 00:06:58,544
Like we're starting over again.

91
00:07:01,130 --> 00:07:02,881
Do I look like I have amnesia?

92
00:07:14,768 --> 00:07:16,019
Are you just now getting to work?

93
00:07:17,646 --> 00:07:19,273
I'm coming back from an interview.

94
00:07:20,232 --> 00:07:22,067
How's the job going?

95
00:07:23,527 --> 00:07:25,112
I'm trying to adjust.

96
00:07:26,697 --> 00:07:30,117
I hear you'll be covering
the baseball game tomorrow.

97
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:31,451
The first pitch, I mean.

98
00:07:31,535 --> 00:07:33,495
Oh, yes.

99
00:07:33,996 --> 00:07:34,997
How about going together?

100
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,541
Excuse me?

101
00:07:37,624 --> 00:07:38,792
I'm sorry.

102
00:07:39,501 --> 00:07:41,211
Did that sound too flirty?

103
00:07:41,295 --> 00:07:42,337
Not at all.

104
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:44,506
I never said that.

105
00:07:44,590 --> 00:07:46,550
That's too bad,
because I meant to sound flirty.

106
00:07:53,473 --> 00:07:54,474
What are you doing?

107
00:07:54,558 --> 00:07:56,602
I want to be that thing you said.

108
00:07:56,685 --> 00:08:00,731
Someone who's decided
to be a good person, no matter what.

109
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:04,818
Mr. Lee, you're a very good person.

110
00:08:04,902 --> 00:08:07,654
It's as if you decided
that you'd always be a good person to me,

111
00:08:07,738 --> 00:08:09,031
no matter what.

112
00:08:11,992 --> 00:08:14,953
Looking back on it,
I really liked what you said.

113
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:19,208
So I really want to try
being that kind of person.

114
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:25,631
If we happen to run into each other
at the baseball stadium tomorrow,

115
00:08:26,632 --> 00:08:29,134
wouldn't that be really nice?

116
00:08:29,885 --> 00:08:31,136
Right, yes.

117
00:08:38,685 --> 00:08:40,145
-Shall I call now?
-Yeah.

118
00:08:41,355 --> 00:08:44,358
-I'll see you tomorrow, then.
-Okay.

119
00:08:48,612 --> 00:08:50,530
-You're late.
-There was traffic.

120
00:08:50,614 --> 00:08:52,366
What were you and Mr. Lee talking about?

121
00:08:52,449 --> 00:08:53,659
He said he'd see you tomorrow.

122
00:08:55,035 --> 00:08:57,371
Do I have to answer that?

123
00:08:57,454 --> 00:08:59,289
Isn't that the purpose of a question?

124
00:09:00,374 --> 00:09:02,125
We were just…

125
00:09:02,709 --> 00:09:04,294
We were talking about some personal stuff.

126
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:19,810
I asked around…

127
00:09:21,687 --> 00:09:23,188
and found out that Se-na turned down

128
00:09:23,272 --> 00:09:26,984
a bunch of movie offers
and took a huge pay cut to do Kang Pil-gu.

129
00:09:27,067 --> 00:09:30,237
Everyone's saying she must really want to
get back together with Hyeon-jun

130
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:33,615
since there's no other reason
she would take a supporting role.

131
00:09:33,699 --> 00:09:36,159
-She says she still has feelings for me.
-What?

132
00:09:36,243 --> 00:09:38,870
-She wants to start over again.
-Seriously?

133
00:09:38,954 --> 00:09:41,290
It looks like she'll turn up
in every project I do.

134
00:09:41,373 --> 00:09:42,916
So what are you going to do?

135
00:09:45,043 --> 00:09:47,587
Now isn't the time to talk about that.

136
00:09:47,671 --> 00:09:49,464
Forget Gwon Se-na for now.

137
00:09:49,548 --> 00:09:51,258
Didn't we agree never to meet again

138
00:09:51,341 --> 00:09:53,677
as director and actor?

139
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:01,768
I know what you're worried about, Mr. Lim.

140
00:10:01,852 --> 00:10:04,813
But things are different now.
I don't have much say in things anymore.

141
00:10:04,896 --> 00:10:08,942
And you said you didn't want to do it
because of Ms. Gwon, not me.

142
00:10:09,026 --> 00:10:10,652
I'm glad you brought that up.

143
00:10:10,736 --> 00:10:14,656
Then drop Ms. Gwon
before you approach me, Director.

144
00:10:14,740 --> 00:10:17,367
Why would I drop a global star like her?

145
00:10:17,993 --> 00:10:18,910
Then how about this?

146
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:23,248
In the first episode,
I chase a suspect in a car

147
00:10:23,332 --> 00:10:25,042
and then get into a huge accident.

148
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:28,378
So I undergo a face swap
and come out completely transformed.

149
00:10:28,462 --> 00:10:31,214
That way, another actor
can take over as Kang Pil-gu.

150
00:10:31,298 --> 00:10:32,341
Mr. Lim.

151
00:10:33,258 --> 00:10:35,677
I'll film up to that scene,
for old times' sake.

152
00:10:38,347 --> 00:10:40,432
I'm sorry to interrupt,

153
00:10:42,184 --> 00:10:45,479
but now's the time to play this.

154
00:10:47,564 --> 00:10:50,233
I, Lim Hyeon-jun, swear to perform

155
00:10:50,317 --> 00:10:51,651
-in season five of Kang Pil-gu,
-Damn you!

156
00:10:51,735 --> 00:10:53,320
no matter what!

157
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:09,294
"Right now, I think it's best
that you continue what you're doing

158
00:11:09,378 --> 00:11:12,923
rather than trying something new."
That's what the cards say.

159
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:14,883
Let's pretend we're meeting
for the first time today.

160
00:11:14,966 --> 00:11:15,967
Like we're starting over again.

161
00:11:16,051 --> 00:11:20,931
I, Lim Hyeon-jun, swear to perform
in season five of Kang Pil-gu,

162
00:11:21,014 --> 00:11:21,932
no matter what!

163
00:11:43,662 --> 00:11:45,372
What was that?

164
00:11:46,498 --> 00:11:50,794
Why did my mind jump to that
for no reason?

165
00:11:50,877 --> 00:11:54,381
Did you think
I was one of the hostesses there?

166
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:06,685
I owe her an apology.

167
00:12:08,019 --> 00:12:09,980
It's really weighing me down.

168
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:13,608
Bro, are you okay?

169
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:18,947
-Mr. Hwang.
-Yeah?

170
00:12:19,573 --> 00:12:21,283
Can you go and apologize
to someone for me?

171
00:12:21,366 --> 00:12:23,285
Bro, apologies
and caring for your folks are on you.

172
00:12:31,918 --> 00:12:35,422
I guess this season will be a megahit
if Gwon Se-na is in it.

173
00:12:38,175 --> 00:12:40,469
-That goes without saying.
-Mr. Hwang.

174
00:12:41,344 --> 00:12:43,013
I'm being serious right now.

175
00:12:43,096 --> 00:12:45,307
If you tell me to do Kang Pil-gu
one more time,

176
00:12:45,390 --> 00:12:46,892
I'll find a different agency.

177
00:12:48,518 --> 00:12:50,854
This is the last time, and I mean it.

178
00:12:52,105 --> 00:12:53,273
Wait, you'll do it?

179
00:12:54,941 --> 00:12:57,194
-Bro, you'll really do it?
-Yeah.

180
00:12:57,277 --> 00:12:59,362
You sure you're okay
working with Gwon Se-na?

181
00:12:59,446 --> 00:13:00,697
Of course, I'm not okay.

182
00:13:01,281 --> 00:13:02,908
But I will be,

183
00:13:02,991 --> 00:13:04,659
because I'm a better person than her.

184
00:13:04,743 --> 00:13:06,328
Good call, bro!

185
00:13:06,411 --> 00:13:08,747
I don't care
if she still has feelings for me.

186
00:13:09,331 --> 00:13:10,415
I'm going to focus on my work.

187
00:13:10,499 --> 00:13:12,959
-I like the serious act.
-It's not an act.

188
00:13:15,837 --> 00:13:17,506
That said,

189
00:13:18,089 --> 00:13:19,758
I have a few conditions.

190
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:21,218
Conditions?

191
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:22,594
-First.
-First.

192
00:13:23,178 --> 00:13:26,640
There will be no romantic storyline
with Gwon Se-na.

193
00:13:26,723 --> 00:13:28,391
No physical intimacy whatsoever.

194
00:13:28,475 --> 00:13:29,309
Second.

195
00:13:30,936 --> 00:13:34,439
Only five scenes
with Gwon Se-na per episode.

196
00:13:34,523 --> 00:13:36,358
No more than that.

197
00:13:36,942 --> 00:13:37,776
Third.

198
00:13:37,859 --> 00:13:39,194
The second unit will start the shoot,

199
00:13:39,277 --> 00:13:43,198
and I'll only work with its director,
not with Director Bak Byeong-gi.

200
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:44,533
Fourth.

201
00:13:44,616 --> 00:13:48,703
After this season, Lim Hyeon-jun
will no longer appear in Kang Pil-gu.

202
00:13:51,248 --> 00:13:52,207
Go ahead and drink it.

203
00:13:52,791 --> 00:13:54,501
You've always wanted to try it.

204
00:14:01,424 --> 00:14:03,051
Those are my conditions.

205
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:05,011
If you agree to these conditions,

206
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:07,973
-he says he'll do it.
-What if we don't?

207
00:14:08,056 --> 00:14:10,225
If you don't agree to them,
then he won't do it.

208
00:14:10,308 --> 00:14:12,978
How about we agree for now
and change our tune later?

209
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:14,604
-Right!
-Right.

210
00:14:14,688 --> 00:14:16,314
If you change your tune,
then he won't do it.

211
00:14:18,358 --> 00:14:19,526
They agreed to the conditions?

212
00:14:19,609 --> 00:14:20,652
All of them?

213
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:23,196
What did Byeong-gi say?

214
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:26,157
Mr. Bak… I guess he's Director Bak now.

215
00:14:26,241 --> 00:14:28,201
Anyway, he agreed to everything.

216
00:14:28,285 --> 00:14:30,787
You know he's not
the two-faced type, right?

217
00:14:30,870 --> 00:14:32,664
I think we can trust him.

218
00:14:32,747 --> 00:14:33,957
He's changed a lot.

219
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:37,586
He's not the same
indie-film-making fanatic anymore.

220
00:14:37,669 --> 00:14:39,629
He takes one-on-one Pilates lessons

221
00:14:39,713 --> 00:14:42,799
and sips 20,000-won coffee
while having brunch.

222
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:45,176
He's not the same Bak Byeong-gi
from back in the day.

223
00:14:45,260 --> 00:14:47,971
Bro, you own a supercar
worth hundreds of millions of won,

224
00:14:48,054 --> 00:14:49,973
while bossing around
the director and production company.

225
00:14:50,056 --> 00:14:53,435
And you eat salad with chicken breast
instead of just fried chicken.

226
00:14:53,977 --> 00:14:55,687
Do you think you're still the same?

227
00:14:55,770 --> 00:14:57,606
Fine, whatever.

228
00:14:57,689 --> 00:15:02,319
Oh, and about that blind date
with no celebrities or reporters…

229
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:06,323
I know someone who's really great.
Should I go ahead and set it up?

230
00:15:06,406 --> 00:15:07,407
A blind date?

231
00:15:08,283 --> 00:15:11,494
Sure, maybe after all this is over.

232
00:15:11,578 --> 00:15:13,038
Jeez, you were begging not too long ago.

233
00:15:13,121 --> 00:15:15,040
Anyway, I'll see you
at the baseball stadium later.

234
00:15:15,123 --> 00:15:16,958
Hey, hold on.

235
00:15:17,042 --> 00:15:20,795
They'll probably send a sports reporter
for today's first pitch event, right?

236
00:15:20,879 --> 00:15:23,590
Hey, bro, I'm getting a call right now.

237
00:15:23,673 --> 00:15:25,300
See you later!

238
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:39,314
You're going on a blind date?

239
00:15:39,397 --> 00:15:41,024
Man, you scared me.

240
00:15:42,984 --> 00:15:44,069
Yeah, so what?

241
00:15:44,152 --> 00:15:46,071
I really liked that reporter.

242
00:15:46,613 --> 00:15:49,908
If you like her that much,
you should go out with her instead.

243
00:15:49,991 --> 00:15:51,910
Have you even seen her before?

244
00:15:51,993 --> 00:15:53,662
I met her when I went to Hong-sin's place.

245
00:15:53,745 --> 00:15:56,206
She seemed really cool
and passionate about her job.

246
00:15:57,332 --> 00:15:58,625
Are you still hanging out with him?

247
00:15:58,708 --> 00:16:01,127
Do I need your permission
to see friends at my age?

248
00:16:04,547 --> 00:16:05,465
And Hyeon-jun.

249
00:16:05,965 --> 00:16:07,801
I'm saying this because I care about you,

250
00:16:07,884 --> 00:16:09,594
but you need to meet someone

251
00:16:09,678 --> 00:16:11,971
who likes you for who you are,
not because you're an actor.

252
00:16:15,850 --> 00:16:18,520
Not that you'd find someone like that
with your sense of judgment.

253
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:24,067
What's wrong with my sense of judgment?

254
00:16:35,704 --> 00:16:37,122
Wow, there are so many people here.

255
00:16:37,205 --> 00:16:39,124
