391
00:24:10,616 --> 00:24:13,411
I'm Lim Hyeon-jun,
the actor who plays Kang Pil-gu

392
00:24:13,494 --> 00:24:14,871
in Good Detective Kang Pil-gu!

393
00:24:15,454 --> 00:24:16,414
Thank you!

394
00:24:30,595 --> 00:24:31,679
He nailed that throw.

395
00:24:34,223 --> 00:24:36,100
It was worth giving him a crash course.

396
00:25:02,585 --> 00:25:04,003
What's wrong? Do you feel ill?

397
00:25:04,879 --> 00:25:06,172
No, I'm okay.

398
00:25:17,350 --> 00:25:18,476
BAHN SOO-JUNG

399
00:25:20,102 --> 00:25:21,145
Mr. Lee.

400
00:25:21,229 --> 00:25:22,438
I'm sorry,

401
00:25:23,231 --> 00:25:25,483
but I won't make it to dinner tonight.

402
00:25:27,735 --> 00:25:28,694
But…

403
00:25:37,620 --> 00:25:39,580
I'm sorry for calling you so suddenly.

404
00:25:40,373 --> 00:25:41,415
It's okay.

405
00:25:43,042 --> 00:25:46,462
But you don't look so well.

406
00:25:46,545 --> 00:25:47,630
I haven't been able to sleep.

407
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:52,134
Soo-jung, is there something
you're hiding from me?

408
00:25:54,428 --> 00:25:55,763
Ms. Wi.

409
00:25:55,846 --> 00:25:57,974
Can you pretend you never saw

410
00:25:58,057 --> 00:26:00,309
the video I handed over to you?

411
00:26:00,393 --> 00:26:03,062
And forget you ever heard
Gwon Se-na's name.

412
00:26:03,604 --> 00:26:05,273
Why? What's going on?

413
00:26:13,030 --> 00:26:13,990
The truth is,

414
00:26:15,366 --> 00:26:17,285
another hostess who was there that night…

415
00:26:18,995 --> 00:26:21,706
asked that man for money.

416
00:26:22,290 --> 00:26:26,502
She thought he and Gwon Se-na were dating,

417
00:26:26,585 --> 00:26:28,921
so she said she'd expose them
if he didn't pay.

418
00:26:29,922 --> 00:26:31,674
But he gave her a huge amount.

419
00:26:31,757 --> 00:26:34,593
She was so scared
that she promised to return the money

420
00:26:34,677 --> 00:26:36,429
and not to expose them.

421
00:26:36,512 --> 00:26:40,474
But he said you can't undo
what's been done,

422
00:26:40,558 --> 00:26:44,353
and that if word gets out,
he'd come after her.

423
00:26:44,437 --> 00:26:47,481
I haven't been able
to reach her since then.

424
00:26:48,482 --> 00:26:49,317
Ms. Wi.

425
00:26:51,068 --> 00:26:53,779
That man is seriously dangerous, isn't he?

426
00:26:56,574 --> 00:26:57,783
If you want this to end,

427
00:26:58,617 --> 00:27:01,329
you have to tell me the truth
about everything.

428
00:27:02,079 --> 00:27:05,207
Everything about that man,
and about Gwon Se-na as well.

429
00:27:13,591 --> 00:27:18,262
When you were at the Geumsang Arts Awards…

430
00:27:19,055 --> 00:27:20,139
That night,

431
00:27:20,765 --> 00:27:23,142
the chairman you asked questions to…

432
00:27:24,643 --> 00:27:25,895
It was him.

433
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,774
That's the man who dated Ms. Gwon Se-na.

434
00:27:53,464 --> 00:27:54,924
EUNSEONGILBO'S CHAIRMAN LEE DAE-HO
AT THE GEUMSANG ARTS AWARDS

435
00:28:26,622 --> 00:28:28,707
LEE DAE-HO

436
00:28:30,668 --> 00:28:31,836
LEE DAE-HO
EUNSEONG GROUP (CHAIRMAN)

437
00:28:33,796 --> 00:28:36,674
YOUNGER BROTHER
LEE JAE-HYEONG

438
00:28:37,925 --> 00:28:40,386
I recently joined Sports Eunseong
as the new president.

439
00:28:40,469 --> 00:28:41,303
Do you run a conglomerate?

440
00:28:41,887 --> 00:28:43,347
My brother's the one who runs it.

441
00:28:43,848 --> 00:28:46,183
I'm just a salaried president.

442
00:28:56,861 --> 00:28:59,989
So the passcode's the same
as your last place.

443
00:29:08,914 --> 00:29:10,082
How did you find this place?

444
00:29:10,166 --> 00:29:11,667
Why pretend to live modestly

445
00:29:12,835 --> 00:29:14,211
when you can be in a mansion?

446
00:29:16,338 --> 00:29:17,173
Get out.

447
00:29:17,256 --> 00:29:20,759
Barging into your ex's place like this
is considered trespassing.

448
00:29:23,387 --> 00:29:24,722
Did we break up?

449
00:29:24,805 --> 00:29:25,931
Why? When?

450
00:29:26,015 --> 00:29:27,349
What are you up to?

451
00:29:27,933 --> 00:29:29,768
If you don't want to break up with me,

452
00:29:29,852 --> 00:29:31,312
then get a divorce.

453
00:29:31,812 --> 00:29:32,897
Hey, Gwon Se-na.

454
00:29:37,443 --> 00:29:38,277
Listen carefully.

455
00:29:38,360 --> 00:29:40,446
You're not stupid,
so I won't repeat myself.

456
00:29:41,071 --> 00:29:44,742
We're an economic community.
You know what that is, right?

457
00:29:45,326 --> 00:29:46,535
That means you and I

458
00:29:46,619 --> 00:29:50,164
