when I have to be around a lot of people.

511
00:32:32,368 --> 00:32:35,287
But I had an attack near the elevator
in my apartment building.

512
00:32:35,371 --> 00:32:36,872
What kind of situation was it?

513
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:39,750
I was with some neighbors I usually greet.

514
00:32:39,833 --> 00:32:42,670
They said something that bothered me,

515
00:32:42,753 --> 00:32:46,173
and the second I heard it,
I couldn't breathe all of a sudden.

516
00:32:46,256 --> 00:32:48,425
I knew I was having another panic attack.

517
00:32:52,554 --> 00:32:53,514
Right, so…

518
00:32:54,848 --> 00:32:56,141
Should I just wrap it up again?

519
00:32:57,184 --> 00:32:59,561
There's no one in the waiting room today,
so you can keep going.

520
00:32:59,645 --> 00:33:00,604
I see.

521
00:33:02,439 --> 00:33:04,024
I've been very curious about this.

522
00:33:04,108 --> 00:33:06,235
How on earth did I get a panic disorder?

523
00:33:06,318 --> 00:33:07,986
I just can't understand it.

524
00:33:08,070 --> 00:33:08,987
In what way?

525
00:33:10,656 --> 00:33:13,992
My career was once ruined
because of a woman,

526
00:33:14,076 --> 00:33:15,577
my mom got into money trouble,

527
00:33:15,661 --> 00:33:18,038
and I had to make money
for my brother's tuition.

528
00:33:18,122 --> 00:33:20,708
Even though I'd stay up all night
binding books at the print shop,

529
00:33:20,791 --> 00:33:22,209
I was totally fine.

530
00:33:22,292 --> 00:33:24,378
I'm in a much better place now
than I was back then.

531
00:33:24,461 --> 00:33:28,132
I can have or do whatever I want,
and I'm living a life anyone would envy.

532
00:33:28,215 --> 00:33:30,759
So how can I get a panic disorder
over something so petty?

533
00:33:30,843 --> 00:33:32,428
If someone like me gets a panic order,

534
00:33:32,511 --> 00:33:35,681
then wouldn't nine out of ten people
in this country have it as well?

535
00:33:35,764 --> 00:33:39,059
It's common for panic to set in
once people return from battle,

536
00:33:39,143 --> 00:33:40,936
rather than during the actual battle.

537
00:33:43,439 --> 00:33:46,358
Then what else can I do
to make myself better

538
00:33:46,442 --> 00:33:48,026
other than taking meds?

539
00:33:48,110 --> 00:33:49,528
Sleep well and eat well.

540
00:33:49,611 --> 00:33:52,698
And avoid drinking
alcohol and coffee for now.

541
00:33:52,781 --> 00:33:54,241
And when it comes to mental health,

542
00:33:54,324 --> 00:33:57,035
it helps to have positive relationships.

543
00:33:58,370 --> 00:33:59,329
Then…

544
00:34:01,707 --> 00:34:03,542
By any chance,

545
00:34:04,376 --> 00:34:06,003
do you think dating…

546
00:34:07,629 --> 00:34:08,839
could be helpful?

547
00:34:11,341 --> 00:34:13,635
Of course, meeting the right person
can definitely help.

548
00:34:13,719 --> 00:34:16,972
But don't expect your panic to get better
just because someone cares for you.

549
00:34:17,055 --> 00:34:19,475
Love is better when it's reciprocated.

550
00:34:19,558 --> 00:34:22,352
It's the same as hyperventilating
if you think about it.

551
00:34:22,436 --> 00:34:26,023
People think that breathing a lot
will make the suffocating feeling go away.

552
00:34:26,106 --> 00:34:28,567
Similarly, people think
that building a bond with someone

553
00:34:28,650 --> 00:34:32,488
and feeling loved and cared for
will make things better.

554
00:34:32,571 --> 00:34:33,989
But that's not true.

555
00:34:34,656 --> 00:34:35,824
Inhale.

556
00:34:37,451 --> 00:34:38,619
And exhale.

557
00:34:40,579 --> 00:34:42,289
Just as we breathe in and out,

558
00:34:42,372 --> 00:34:45,626
love has to be both given and received.

559
00:34:55,344 --> 00:34:56,512
Hello.

560
00:34:56,595 --> 00:34:59,723
Hello, it's nice to meet you.

561
00:34:59,807 --> 00:35:00,974
Nice to meet you too.

562
00:35:01,892 --> 00:35:04,186
Mr. Lim, what's your MBTI type?

563
00:35:05,813 --> 00:35:07,314
My MBTI type?

564
00:35:07,981 --> 00:35:10,609
Well, I'm INFJ--

565
00:35:10,692 --> 00:35:12,569
No, you're INTP.

566
00:35:13,570 --> 00:35:14,404
Is that so?

567
00:35:15,405 --> 00:35:16,532
You know better than I do.

568
00:35:16,615 --> 00:35:20,661
You're naturally very energetic
and can't stand injustice.

569
00:35:20,744 --> 00:35:24,081
So I thought you were an extrovert,
but you're the total opposite.

570
00:35:24,164 --> 00:35:25,624
I see.

571
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:30,420
Well, that's because Kang Pil-gu
is just a character I play.

572
00:35:31,004 --> 00:35:32,256
Where do you live, Mr. Lim?

573
00:35:32,339 --> 00:35:34,591
Oh, I live--

574
00:35:34,675 --> 00:35:37,594
I saw online
that you live in the Hannam Dia.

575
00:35:38,178 --> 00:35:39,930
Isn't that place super expensive?

576
00:35:42,516 --> 00:35:43,892
That information shows up online?

577
00:35:43,976 --> 00:35:45,561
Yes, of course.

578
00:35:46,812 --> 00:35:49,189
Have you met Byeon Woo-seok?
How about Cha Eun-woo?

579
00:35:49,273 --> 00:35:51,191
I bet they're so handsome in person.

580
00:35:52,276 --> 00:35:54,361
Yes, of course.

581
00:35:54,987 --> 00:35:55,821
Right.

582
00:35:55,904 --> 00:35:57,990
Are you really Lim Hyeon-jun?

583
00:35:58,574 --> 00:36:00,826
I'm such a huge fan!

584
00:36:00,909 --> 00:36:03,829
I watched every season of Kang Pil-gu.

585
00:36:03,912 --> 00:36:04,997
-Thank you--
-Snap!

586
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:06,498
"They say you can't fix people."

587
00:36:06,582 --> 00:36:07,708
"But I do."

588
00:36:07,791 --> 00:36:08,917
That's the line, right?

589
00:36:09,793 --> 00:36:10,752
Yes, right.

590
00:36:12,880 --> 00:36:15,299
Gosh, it feels like
I should give you an autograph.

591
00:36:15,382 --> 00:36:17,342
Yes, please. And I want a photo.

592
00:36:17,426 --> 00:36:19,803
I can post it on my social media, right?
Thanks!

593
00:36:19,887 --> 00:36:21,096
Hold on, I…

594
00:36:21,179 --> 00:36:22,097
Smile!

595
00:36:31,315 --> 00:36:33,275
Mr. Lim, did you get home safely?

596
00:36:33,358 --> 00:36:37,070
It was a real pleasure and honor
to meet you today.

597
00:36:39,072 --> 00:36:40,657
Honor, my ass.

598
00:36:43,452 --> 00:36:44,703
Hyeon-jun, are you home?

599
00:36:47,122 --> 00:36:50,542
Hey, how do kids these days
meet people to date?

600
00:36:50,626 --> 00:36:51,627
Why do you ask?

601
00:36:52,961 --> 00:36:55,505
My friends use dating apps.

602
00:36:57,132 --> 00:36:58,216
Dating apps?

603
00:36:59,885 --> 00:37:01,053
What's the world coming to?

604
00:37:01,136 --> 00:37:04,306
It won't be long
before AI takes over the world.

605
00:37:04,389 --> 00:37:06,391
You're one to talk.
Su-ji is your best friend.

606
00:37:06,475 --> 00:37:09,519
And people used to meet as pen pals
and then get married.

607
00:37:09,603 --> 00:37:12,105
Focus on your studies
instead of lecturing me, you punk.

608
00:37:12,940 --> 00:37:13,774
Jeez.

609
00:37:15,317 --> 00:37:17,736
By the way, what's in those boxes?

610
00:37:19,446 --> 00:37:21,406
Those are the rice cookers that I promote.

611
00:37:21,490 --> 00:37:23,951
The advertiser sent them as a gift,
but I have no one to give them to.

612
00:37:24,910 --> 00:37:26,244
They look expensive.

613
00:37:26,828 --> 00:37:28,080
Can I sell them on Onion?

614
00:37:29,122 --> 00:37:30,123
Onion?

615
00:37:30,916 --> 00:37:32,417
Oh, that secondhand platform?

616
00:37:33,251 --> 00:37:35,128
-Do whatever you want.
-Awesome.

617
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:38,090
Oh, right.

618
00:37:38,173 --> 00:37:40,968
-My account got suspended.
-Why?

619
00:37:41,051 --> 00:37:43,595
I sold a few of the down jackets
you received as gifts,

620
00:37:43,679 --> 00:37:45,555
and someone reported me
as a commercial seller.

621
00:37:46,556 --> 00:37:48,642
Oh, boy.

622
00:37:49,142 --> 00:37:50,227
Let me borrow your phone.

623
00:37:52,688 --> 00:37:55,273
Hey, how do you know my passcode?

624
00:37:56,358 --> 00:37:57,567
It's my birthday.

625
00:38:02,114 --> 00:38:03,490
ENTER NICKNAME: KANG PIL-GU
NICKNAME TAKEN

626
00:38:03,573 --> 00:38:04,866
Why are there so many Kang Pil-gus?

627
00:38:04,950 --> 00:38:06,201
What are you doing?

628
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:09,204
I downloaded the Onion app,
but there are too many Kang Pil-gus.

629
00:38:09,287 --> 00:38:10,247
This won't do.

630
00:38:12,541 --> 00:38:16,128
How much of my stuff did you sell
for your account to get suspended?

631
00:38:19,548 --> 00:38:20,382
Hey!

632
00:38:20,882 --> 00:38:23,427
What are you doing with my phone?

633
00:38:31,309 --> 00:38:33,562
Of course, meeting the right person
can definitely help.

634
00:38:38,525 --> 00:38:39,943
You need to meet someone

635
00:38:40,027 --> 00:38:41,862
who likes you for who you are,
not because you're an actor.

636
00:38:47,284 --> 00:38:48,243
Onion!

637
00:38:57,210 --> 00:38:58,670
What, already?

638
00:38:58,754 --> 00:39:01,798
Hello, do you still have the rice cooker?

639
00:39:01,882 --> 00:39:03,508
Of course, I do.

640
00:39:04,134 --> 00:39:07,554
-Yes, I do.
-Can you give me a 30,000 won discount?

641
00:39:08,305 --> 00:39:09,347
Thirty thousand won?

642
00:39:10,807 --> 00:39:13,435
Sure, do whatever you want.

643
00:39:13,518 --> 00:39:14,728
Yes, I can do that.

644
00:39:16,855 --> 00:39:20,150
That punk set my nickname as "Melomaster."

645
00:39:20,233 --> 00:39:21,068
SOULISHERE, MELOMASTER

646
00:39:26,948 --> 00:39:28,158
Melomaster…

647
00:39:28,658 --> 00:39:31,953
Can I get a veggie sandwich
on Parmesan oregano bread

648
00:39:32,037 --> 00:39:35,040
with lettuce, tomato, cucumber,
bell peppers, and onion?

649
00:39:35,123 --> 00:39:37,876
And the sauce… Can you recommend one?

650
00:39:37,959 --> 00:39:39,211
-Sure thing.
-Thank you.

651
00:39:45,801 --> 00:39:48,261
Wow, I went with your suggestion,
and it tastes great!

652
00:39:48,345 --> 00:39:51,014
See? I eat this all the time
when I'm on a diet.

653
00:39:52,265 --> 00:39:55,102
By the way, how did the blind dates go?

654
00:39:55,811 --> 00:39:57,354
They were okay, I guess.

655
00:39:57,437 --> 00:39:59,272
What's wrong? You didn't like any of them?

656
00:40:00,148 --> 00:40:02,526
No, it just felt like

657
00:40:03,318 --> 00:40:05,737
I was holding one-on-one fan meetings.

658
00:40:06,822 --> 00:40:08,323
This is all your fault!

659
00:40:08,406 --> 00:40:11,535
I need to be in rom-coms or melodramas
if I want a dating life!

660
00:40:12,744 --> 00:40:15,122
Why do you always blame me for everything?

661
00:40:15,664 --> 00:40:17,082
Seriously. Oh, right.

662
00:40:17,165 --> 00:40:19,334
The article about you doing Kang Pil-gu
is going out today.

663
00:40:19,417 --> 00:40:21,837
-That's okay, right?
-Yeah.

664
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,964
I'm meeting the chief of Sports Eunseong
and Ms. Wi.

665
00:40:24,047 --> 00:40:24,965
Are you coming?

666
00:40:25,549 --> 00:40:26,800
Do I have to be there?

667
00:40:26,883 --> 00:40:29,052
I guess you're busy
with the commercial shoot.

668
00:40:30,220 --> 00:40:33,932
Did you think
I was one of the hostesses there?

669
00:40:34,516 --> 00:40:35,433
Actually, no.

670
00:40:37,435 --> 00:40:38,812
I'll make some time.

671
00:40:38,895 --> 00:40:40,397
Okay, then.

672
00:40:59,332 --> 00:41:00,542
-Hello?
-It's me.

673
00:41:01,376 --> 00:41:02,335
Thank you.

674
00:41:03,170 --> 00:41:04,379
Don't thank me.

675
00:41:06,214 --> 00:41:08,758
I'm not doing it
because you still have feelings for me.

676
00:41:09,718 --> 00:41:12,804
I just don't want to
sink to your level as a person.

677
00:41:13,722 --> 00:41:14,890
So don't take it the wrong way.

678
00:41:18,476 --> 00:41:19,895
-Are you listening?
-Yeah.

679
00:41:20,604 --> 00:41:22,022
I heard everything you said.

680
00:41:22,105 --> 00:41:23,481
I'll call you later.

681
00:41:30,614 --> 00:41:31,823
Oh, hey.

682
00:41:33,325 --> 00:41:34,910
-The director wants to explain
-Yeah?

683
00:41:34,993 --> 00:41:36,578
the concept for today's shoot,

684
00:41:36,661 --> 00:41:38,038
-so he's waiting outside.
-Oh, okay.

685
00:41:38,121 --> 00:41:39,497
-Tell him to come in.
-Okay.

686
00:41:39,581 --> 00:41:41,750
But he mentioned the concept has changed.

687
00:41:41,833 --> 00:41:44,127
-Yeah, okay.
-Is that okay?

688
00:41:44,211 --> 00:41:46,046
-Yes, tell him to come in.
-All right.

689
00:41:46,129 --> 00:41:47,547
-Right, Gil-su.
-Yes?

690
00:41:47,631 --> 00:41:49,007
Today's shoot will finish
before 6 p.m., right?

691
00:41:49,090 --> 00:41:51,384
-Yes, likely so.
-Good.

692
00:41:54,846 --> 00:41:55,680
Director.

693
00:41:56,431 --> 00:41:58,183
Hello, Mr. Lim!

694
00:41:58,266 --> 00:42:00,685
-Hello.
-It's an honor to work with you again.

695
00:42:00,769 --> 00:42:03,021
Not at all. I look forward to it.

696
00:42:03,104 --> 00:42:05,065
Let me explain the concept for the shoot.

697
00:42:05,148 --> 00:42:07,651
-Did something change?
-Just a little bit.

698
00:42:07,734 --> 00:42:10,195
-I see.
-If you see here, this is a ballet outfit…

699
00:42:10,278 --> 00:42:11,696
Hold on.

700
00:42:13,365 --> 00:42:15,742
I really shouldn't eat
since I'm on a diet.

701
00:42:15,825 --> 00:42:17,577
If it's tasty, it's zero calories!

702
00:42:18,411 --> 00:42:19,537
Why is this so salty?

703
00:42:19,621 --> 00:42:22,290
I might kick the bucket eating this.

704
00:42:22,374 --> 00:42:23,291
Sir.

705
00:42:23,375 --> 00:42:25,961
Artisan Ramyeon's soup is light and mild,

706
00:42:26,044 --> 00:42:27,963
so you won't kick the bucket!

707
00:42:28,046 --> 00:42:30,715
Man, I'm kind of hungry.

708
00:42:31,508 --> 00:42:34,094
But I'll probably regret eating ramyeon.

709
00:42:34,678 --> 00:42:37,681
Detective, if you don't eat it now,
you'll regret it until tomorrow.

710
00:42:37,764 --> 00:42:38,848
ARTISAN RAMYEON
MILD FLAVOR

711
00:42:41,559 --> 00:42:44,396
Worried it's nighttime?
Worried it's past midnight?

712
00:42:44,479 --> 00:42:47,524
Don't worry
Artisan Ramyeon is all good

713
00:42:47,607 --> 00:42:50,735
You can enjoy it without worries

714
00:42:50,819 --> 00:42:53,405
Tasty Artisan Ramyeon

715
00:42:53,488 --> 00:42:55,448
Let's all enjoy Artisan Ramyeon

716
00:42:55,532 --> 00:42:56,658
Artisan!

717
00:42:56,741 --> 00:42:57,867
I'm not doing it!

718
00:42:57,951 --> 00:42:59,744
Wearing a ramyeon packet costume
is bad enough as it is!

719
00:42:59,828 --> 00:43:02,038
Why does it always have to end
with Kang Pil-gu?

720
00:43:02,122 --> 00:43:05,625
Call Mr. Hwang, damn it.
Tell him I won't do this commercial!

721
00:43:05,709 --> 00:43:07,252
Come on, please. They'll kill me.

722
00:43:07,335 --> 00:43:09,462
Don't look at me like that.
I'm not doing it.

723
00:43:10,046 --> 00:43:11,756
If it's tasty, it's zero calories.

724
00:43:12,382 --> 00:43:13,883
Artisan Ramyeon is…

725
00:43:14,467 --> 00:43:16,469
Cut! Let's go again.

726
00:43:26,730 --> 00:43:28,023
I'm sorry.

727
00:43:28,106 --> 00:43:30,358
Something urgent came up,
and the chief won't make it.

728
00:43:30,442 --> 00:43:31,985
Oh, really?

729
00:43:32,068 --> 00:43:34,946
Mr. Lim Hyeon-jun is filming
a ramyeon commercial right now.

730
00:43:35,030 --> 00:43:37,991
The shoot is running longer than expected,
so he might not be able to make it.

731
00:43:38,074 --> 00:43:39,117
I'm so sorry about this.

732
00:43:39,200 --> 00:43:40,076
It's okay.

733
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:43,121
-Please go ahead and order.
-Thank you.

734
00:43:44,581 --> 00:43:46,541
Let's all enjoy Artisan Ramyeon

735
00:43:46,624 --> 00:43:47,959
Artisan!

736
00:43:48,043 --> 00:43:49,044
Cut!

737
00:43:49,127 --> 00:43:51,546
We're losing steam, guys.

738
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:52,547
Let's go again!

739
00:43:54,174 --> 00:43:55,050
Ready.

740
00:44:04,809 --> 00:44:06,728
…Artisan Ramyeon has chewy noodles,

741
00:44:06,811 --> 00:44:09,606
and the soup is absolutely delicious!

742
00:44:10,231 --> 00:44:11,066
Cut!

743
00:44:13,860 --> 00:44:15,195
Let's take a break, everyone!

744
00:44:28,708 --> 00:44:30,835
-Hyeon-jun, it's time to head back in.
-Okay.

745
00:44:31,920 --> 00:44:33,254
What time is it, Gil-su?

746
00:44:33,755 --> 00:44:34,589
It's 6 o'clock.

747
00:44:36,466 --> 00:44:37,717
-It's 6 o'clock?
-Yes.

748
00:44:37,801 --> 00:44:39,344
Let's film this already.

749
00:44:42,722 --> 00:44:43,723
I got this!

750
00:44:43,807 --> 00:44:45,892
-Yes!
-Let's go.

751
00:44:47,143 --> 00:44:50,647
Detective, if you don't eat it now,
you'll regret it until tomorrow

752
00:44:50,730 --> 00:44:54,651
because Artisan Ramyeon has chewy noodles,
and the soup is absolutely delicious!

753
00:44:54,734 --> 00:44:57,904
Cut! Great job. That's a wrap!

754
00:45:01,157 --> 00:45:02,075
Great job!

755
00:45:02,700 --> 00:45:03,910
Hey, help me with this.

756
00:45:03,993 --> 00:45:05,245
Let's hurry up and go!

757
00:45:07,705 --> 00:45:08,957
-Gil-su.
-Yes?

758
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:10,208
How much further?

759
00:45:10,291 --> 00:45:12,043
We're almost there.

760
00:45:12,127 --> 00:45:14,254
All right. Just hurry, okay?

761
00:45:15,171 --> 00:45:16,214
How much longer?

762
00:45:16,297 --> 00:45:19,050
Not that much,
but the estimated time keeps increasing.

763
00:45:19,134 --> 00:45:20,009
Let's hurry up, okay?

764
00:45:20,093 --> 00:45:22,178
-I'll go as fast as I can.
-Okay, hurry up.

765
00:45:30,145 --> 00:45:32,063
Go ahead and leave!

766
00:45:32,147 --> 00:45:34,315
Wait, not there! It's over here.

767
00:45:36,860 --> 00:45:37,694
Okay, go home!

768
00:45:38,528 --> 00:45:39,654
What's the matter with him?

769
00:45:44,117 --> 00:45:47,704
Ms. Wi, the reason I wanted to see you…

770
00:45:48,538 --> 00:45:50,540
Oh, here you are.

771
00:45:50,623 --> 00:45:52,625
What? Is the shoot over?

772
00:45:52,709 --> 00:45:54,752
-Bro, how did you--
-Hey, bro.

773
00:45:54,836 --> 00:45:58,756
Come on, bro. Take a seat.

774
00:45:58,840 --> 00:46:00,967
-But Hyeon-jun--
-Come on, bro.

775
00:46:01,050 --> 00:46:03,094
-How did you get here, Hyeon-jun?
-Well…

776
00:46:03,178 --> 00:46:04,762
I thought the shoot was running late.

777
00:46:06,389 --> 00:46:07,432
Well…

778
00:46:07,515 --> 00:46:10,518
The shoot ended early
because it turned out well, bro.

779
00:46:10,602 --> 00:46:11,978
Oh, I see.

780
00:46:12,562 --> 00:46:14,272
Right, little bro.

781
00:46:14,355 --> 00:46:16,524
-There wasn't any traffic on the way?
-None at all.

782
00:46:16,608 --> 00:46:18,151
Right, I see.

783
00:46:21,613 --> 00:46:22,489
It's been a while.

784
00:46:22,572 --> 00:46:23,907
Yes, hello.

785
00:46:25,033 --> 00:46:26,534
I thought you couldn't make it.

786
00:46:26,618 --> 00:46:28,411
No, I made it.

787
00:46:30,079 --> 00:46:31,289
Since it's about me,

788
00:46:31,372 --> 00:46:34,584
I came here to tell you myself.

789
00:46:40,673 --> 00:46:42,634
-Bro, did you tell her already?
-Tell her what?

790
00:46:42,717 --> 00:46:44,761
-My news.
-No, not at all.

791
00:46:44,844 --> 00:46:47,096
-Go ahead and tell her.
-Okay.

792
00:46:48,056 --> 00:46:49,390
Oh, I'm getting a call.

793
00:46:49,474 --> 00:46:51,142
-I have to take this.
-Okay.

794
00:47:06,074 --> 00:47:07,200
Have you been well?

795
00:47:08,409 --> 00:47:09,619
Yes.

796
00:47:10,411 --> 00:47:11,329
Right.

797
00:47:12,580 --> 00:47:14,624
-Have you been doing well?
-Yes.

798
00:47:15,124 --> 00:47:16,501
Of course, I have.

799
00:47:18,628 --> 00:47:21,422
Ms. Wi, I'm terribly sorry.

800
00:47:21,506 --> 00:47:23,049
Something urgent came up,
so I have to leave right now.

801
00:47:23,132 --> 00:47:24,884
The keywords for the article…

802
00:47:24,968 --> 00:47:26,553
Right. Little bro, you can tell her.

803
00:47:26,636 --> 00:47:27,929
-Me?
-Yes, that's right.

804
00:47:28,012 --> 00:47:30,056
I'll see you later, then.

805
00:47:30,139 --> 00:47:31,766
-Hey, but--
-Later!

806
00:47:35,478 --> 00:47:37,105
Oh, go ahead.

807
00:47:38,648 --> 00:47:41,526
What's the rush?

808
00:47:42,193 --> 00:47:44,153
Let's eat before we begin.

809
00:47:46,364 --> 00:47:48,199
But I'm done with dessert.

810
00:47:53,162 --> 00:47:54,872
I haven't eaten yet, though.

811
00:47:55,373 --> 00:48:00,336
The last order was 8 o'clock,
so the kitchen is already closed.

812
00:48:00,420 --> 00:48:02,088
I'm very sorry, sir.

813
00:48:03,756 --> 00:48:05,466
Do you know any nearby restaurants?

814
00:48:08,803 --> 00:48:10,722
My manager drives me around everywhere,

815
00:48:11,806 --> 00:48:15,810
and I've been on a diet lately,
so I don't know any good restaurants.

816
00:48:16,811 --> 00:48:17,854
I know a place we can go.

817
00:48:18,521 --> 00:48:19,355
Where…

818
00:48:21,190 --> 00:48:22,609
It's dark

819
00:48:23,026 --> 00:48:24,444
and secluded.

820
00:48:28,615 --> 00:48:29,574
Jeez.

821
00:48:30,199 --> 00:48:34,329
Only teenagers come here
to eat ramyeon and make memories over it.

822
00:48:34,412 --> 00:48:36,623
I can't believe I'm doing this at my age.

823
00:48:37,206 --> 00:48:38,875
Then would you be okay
if someone took a photo

824
00:48:39,459 --> 00:48:41,377
of just the two of us eating at this hour?

825
00:48:44,756 --> 00:48:47,091
At least you got me
the ramyeon I'm promoting.

826
00:48:50,428 --> 00:48:53,222
You never watched Kang Pil-gu
or showed any interest in me,

827
00:48:53,306 --> 00:48:54,974
so how did you know to get this?

828
00:48:55,975 --> 00:48:56,809
It was a coincidence.

829
00:49:00,355 --> 00:49:04,025
Now, go ahead and tell me.
What's the story?

830
00:49:07,904 --> 00:49:11,574
Season five of Kang Pil-gu
has been confirmed.

831
00:49:12,075 --> 00:49:14,827
And Gwon Se-na is joining the cast.

832
00:49:16,663 --> 00:49:19,666
I guess it's good for the drama
that a global star is on board,

833
00:49:19,749 --> 00:49:22,877
but the main character has been
and always will be Kang Pil-gu.

834
00:49:22,960 --> 00:49:24,921
I don't want my fans to worry
that her character

835
00:49:25,004 --> 00:49:26,631
will take the spotlight from mine.

836
00:49:27,632 --> 00:49:29,425
Work that into the article, will you?

837
00:49:33,262 --> 00:49:34,806
I'll get started on the article.

838
00:50:26,858 --> 00:50:28,109
-What is it?
-What?

839
00:50:29,235 --> 00:50:30,278
Do you have something to say?

840
00:50:30,987 --> 00:50:31,821
No.

841
00:50:35,032 --> 00:50:35,992
Well,

842
00:50:36,993 --> 00:50:38,202
I'm thirsty.

843
00:50:38,703 --> 00:50:39,746
So?

844
00:50:44,625 --> 00:50:45,710
Do you have any water?

845
00:50:48,838 --> 00:50:49,756
I don't.

846
00:50:55,052 --> 00:50:55,887
Is your foot okay?

847
00:50:58,014 --> 00:51:00,933
You hurt your foot
breaking the window to help me.

848
00:51:01,017 --> 00:51:03,227
Wait, you remember that?

849
00:51:04,854 --> 00:51:05,688
Vaguely.

850
00:51:07,106 --> 00:51:09,150
It healed a long time ago.

851
00:51:09,984 --> 00:51:11,110
It's fine.

852
00:51:16,699 --> 00:51:17,658
So…

853
00:51:20,286 --> 00:51:21,204
I have

854
00:51:22,705 --> 00:51:24,165
something to say.

855
00:51:31,756 --> 00:51:32,799
I'm sorry about before.

856
00:51:36,344 --> 00:51:38,054
For assuming that you worked as a hostess.

857
00:51:40,097 --> 00:51:41,182
I apologize for that.

858
00:51:54,028 --> 00:51:55,822
Hey, say something.

859
00:51:55,905 --> 00:51:59,700
I'm offering a sincere apology,
and I'm totally embarrassed.

860
00:51:59,784 --> 00:52:02,495
Do I have to accept your apology?

861
00:52:04,038 --> 00:52:04,997
Excuse me?

862
00:52:05,081 --> 00:52:06,082
I mean,

863
00:52:07,166 --> 00:52:09,335
it's only natural to accept an apology

864
00:52:09,418 --> 00:52:11,170
if someone owns up to their mistake.

865
00:52:11,254 --> 00:52:14,173
I didn't do anything unforgivable.
It was just a misunderstanding.

866
00:52:14,966 --> 00:52:17,635
It's only natural to apologize
if you did something wrong.

867
00:52:18,219 --> 00:52:19,971
But accepting the apology
is up to the other person.

868
00:52:20,763 --> 00:52:21,848
Unbelievable.

869
00:52:21,931 --> 00:52:24,892
I forgave you
for storming into the bathroom stall

870
00:52:24,976 --> 00:52:27,812
and humiliating me
while I was taking care of business.

871
00:52:27,895 --> 00:52:30,648
I even forgave you for spying on me
in my hospital room

872
00:52:30,731 --> 00:52:32,316
and gave you an exclusive.

873
00:52:32,400 --> 00:52:34,902
And I let you off the hook
for that article about my mom.

874
00:52:34,986 --> 00:52:36,404
You know what?

875
00:52:36,487 --> 00:52:40,199
After saying all that out loud,
I sound like a complete doormat!

876
00:52:40,700 --> 00:52:41,701
So?

877
00:52:42,743 --> 00:52:44,537
You really won't accept my apology?

878
00:52:45,538 --> 00:52:47,456
Even though
I'm personally giving you an exclusive

879
00:52:47,540 --> 00:52:49,208
and expressing how sorry I am?

880
00:52:49,292 --> 00:52:50,167
That's right.

881
00:52:51,961 --> 00:52:53,129
I don't want your apology.

882
00:53:07,018 --> 00:53:08,352
Seriously?

883
00:53:12,565 --> 00:53:15,067
Stop glaring at me and focus on the road!

884
00:53:15,151 --> 00:53:17,403
I have every right to glare at you!

885
00:53:19,113 --> 00:53:20,573
I forgot my wife's birthday today

886
00:53:20,656 --> 00:53:23,993
and finally got her to forgive me
after begging for hours,

887
00:53:24,076 --> 00:53:25,661
but then you called me back out!

888
00:53:25,745 --> 00:53:28,122
Gil-su couldn't come
because he was drinking!

889
00:53:28,205 --> 00:53:30,750
You could've called a driver
instead of your CEO!

890
00:53:30,833 --> 00:53:32,376
Or you could've driven yourself!

891
00:53:32,460 --> 00:53:34,962
I called you
because I have so much pent-up rage!

892
00:53:35,880 --> 00:53:36,881
Jeez.

893
00:53:39,175 --> 00:53:41,427
What is it now?
Did you fight again with Ms. Wi?

894
00:53:41,510 --> 00:53:43,304
Who said we had a fight?

895
00:53:43,387 --> 00:53:46,223
I apologized for thinking
that she worked as a hostess,

896
00:53:46,307 --> 00:53:48,142
but she wouldn't accept my apology.

897
00:53:48,225 --> 00:53:51,270
I bet you acted all high and mighty
and gave a lousy apology.

898
00:53:51,354 --> 00:53:55,107
That's not true. I gave a sincere apology
for the first time in a while.

899
00:53:56,984 --> 00:53:58,152
Onion!

900
00:53:58,736 --> 00:53:59,695
What was that?

901
00:54:00,863 --> 00:54:02,239
Are you on Onion?

902
00:54:03,032 --> 00:54:05,159
I put something up for Seon-u, that's all.

903
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:08,037
Seriously, the things you do…

904
00:54:23,344 --> 00:54:24,387
Go wash up and sleep.

905
00:54:24,470 --> 00:54:25,805
How are you getting home?

906
00:54:26,514 --> 00:54:29,266
I'm taking a taxi, of course.
You think I'll rent a scooter instead?

907
00:54:31,227 --> 00:54:32,061
Here.

908
00:54:33,020 --> 00:54:33,854
What's that?

909
00:54:34,438 --> 00:54:37,149
-Your wife's birthday gift.
-What?

910
00:54:39,110 --> 00:54:40,569
-What's this?
-Press the button.

911
00:54:49,745 --> 00:54:52,581
It's a bribe to keep her
from divorcing you over me.

912
00:54:53,791 --> 00:54:55,876
Oh, bro!

913
00:54:55,960 --> 00:54:59,130
-Bro, thanks so much!
-Jeez, go away.

914
00:54:59,213 --> 00:55:00,840
Gosh, would you look at that?

915
00:55:02,049 --> 00:55:04,969
Holy cow, it's a luxury car!

916
00:55:05,052 --> 00:55:07,513
I finally get to ride in one of these!

917
00:55:11,726 --> 00:55:12,893
Jeez.

918
00:55:14,687 --> 00:55:15,771
Are you home?

919
00:55:21,902 --> 00:55:22,987
Are you scared?

920
00:55:25,656 --> 00:55:26,991
GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU 2

921
00:55:27,074 --> 00:55:28,409
Damn it.

922
00:55:33,080 --> 00:55:34,749
Change your clothes first.

923
00:55:34,832 --> 00:55:36,542
I think I caught a cold.

924
00:55:36,625 --> 00:55:37,543
You caught a cold?

925
00:55:39,253 --> 00:55:41,172
That's why you need to dress warmly.

926
00:55:42,673 --> 00:55:43,758
Drink some water.

927
00:55:44,508 --> 00:55:45,551
Okay.

928
00:55:46,177 --> 00:55:48,220
Jeez, you're such a handful.

929
00:55:52,600 --> 00:55:55,061
Take two of these before you go to bed.

930
00:56:02,151 --> 00:56:03,235
What a bummer.

931
00:56:03,319 --> 00:56:04,987
I heard my bro Pil-gu
went on a blind date.

932
00:56:05,654 --> 00:56:07,239
-A blind date?
-Yeah.

933
00:56:07,323 --> 00:56:08,741
-With whom?
-How should I know?

934
00:56:08,824 --> 00:56:10,618
He probably has women lining up for him.

935
00:56:10,701 --> 00:56:12,244
Are you going to write about that too?

936
00:56:13,996 --> 00:56:16,916
I mean, it'd be better if I wrote it
and build up my track record.

937
00:56:16,999 --> 00:56:18,793
Jeez, you're really something.

938
00:56:19,376 --> 00:56:21,253
Don't you regret missing out on him?

939
00:56:21,337 --> 00:56:23,923
I mean, he's got the face,
the body, and the fame.

940
00:56:24,507 --> 00:56:25,508
Listen.

941
00:56:26,383 --> 00:56:27,384
How would you feel

942
00:56:28,344 --> 00:56:30,096
if you gave someone a genuine apology,

943
00:56:31,597 --> 00:56:33,057
but they refused to accept it?

944
00:56:35,559 --> 00:56:37,686
Did they do something really terrible?

945
00:56:39,980 --> 00:56:42,358
No, it wasn't that bad.

946
00:56:42,441 --> 00:56:44,777
I'd cut ties with them, then.

947
00:56:48,739 --> 00:56:51,742
Was it you who apologized,
or was it the other way around?

948
00:56:52,743 --> 00:56:53,661
It was me.

949
00:56:55,162 --> 00:56:56,455
I didn't accept the apology.

950
00:56:56,539 --> 00:56:57,414
Why not?

951
00:57:00,334 --> 00:57:01,836
Because when you accept an apology,

952
00:57:03,045 --> 00:57:04,255
it makes you expect more.

953
00:57:06,841 --> 00:57:09,301
That they'll treat you nicer,

954
00:57:09,385 --> 00:57:11,262
or that they'll be friendlier to you.

955
00:57:12,930 --> 00:57:15,015
It was never going to work out anyway,

956
00:57:16,559 --> 00:57:18,686
so I figured
I'd nip that expectation in the bud.

957
00:57:22,439 --> 00:57:24,108
Do you know what people call that?

958
00:57:24,733 --> 00:57:25,568
Putting up walls.

959
00:57:26,610 --> 00:57:28,445
If you keep putting up walls like that,

960
00:57:28,529 --> 00:57:30,698
you'll live alone forever.

961
00:57:30,781 --> 00:57:32,950
Whatever. I'm not taking these.

962
00:57:40,124 --> 00:57:42,126
-Hey, Su-ji.
-Yes?

963
00:57:43,377 --> 00:57:46,797
I've been in a bad mood
since this morning.

964
00:57:47,381 --> 00:57:48,257
Again?

965
00:57:50,426 --> 00:57:51,719
What do you mean "again"?

966
00:57:57,057 --> 00:58:00,853
Why would someone not accept an apology?

967
00:58:02,313 --> 00:58:04,481
I can't think of a good response.

968
00:58:06,901 --> 00:58:08,444
It figures.

969
00:58:08,527 --> 00:58:11,947
If I don't know the answer to that,
how would an AI assistant like you know?

970
00:58:23,417 --> 00:58:24,710
SPORTS EUNSEONG
WI JEONG-SIN

971
00:58:29,423 --> 00:58:31,300
Jeez, did I really catch a cold?

972
00:58:34,511 --> 00:58:35,930
My throat hurts too.

973
00:58:45,606 --> 00:58:46,857
"GOOD DETECTIVE KANG PIL-GU SEASON 5
PRODUCTION CONFIRMED"

974
00:58:46,941 --> 00:58:48,359
"GLOBAL STAR GWON SE-NA JOINS CAST"

975
00:58:51,111 --> 00:58:52,321
I don't want your apology.

976
00:58:54,114 --> 00:58:56,367
Hey, I read an article
about Gwon Se-na joining your drama.

977
00:58:56,450 --> 00:58:57,618
Is it true?

978
00:58:58,202 --> 00:58:59,536
Right.

979
00:58:59,620 --> 00:59:02,248
So you read the article.

980
00:59:02,331 --> 00:59:05,084
You couldn't stand her at all.
Are you getting back together?

981
00:59:05,668 --> 00:59:06,543
Are you crazy?

982
00:59:06,627 --> 00:59:08,712
I'm just keeping
work and personal life separate.

983
00:59:10,631 --> 00:59:11,840
Where are you going anyway?

984
00:59:12,508 --> 00:59:15,719
My friend's grandfather passed away,
so I'm going to the funeral.

985
00:59:17,137 --> 00:59:20,015
But you've got an Onion deal today!

986
00:59:20,099 --> 00:59:21,016
The rice cooker!

987
00:59:21,100 --> 00:59:22,393
That's right.

988
00:59:22,476 --> 00:59:24,061
-It's almost time.
-Jeez.

989
00:59:24,144 --> 00:59:25,604
Can you go instead?

990
00:59:26,772 --> 00:59:28,607
I can't go out and sell a rice cooker.

991
00:59:28,691 --> 00:59:30,276
Everyone knows my face.

992
00:59:30,359 --> 00:59:31,527
It's dark out.

993
00:59:31,610 --> 00:59:32,945
Cover your face,
and nobody will recognize you.

994
00:59:33,028 --> 00:59:36,031
-No, absolutely not.
-My friend's waiting downstairs.

995
00:59:36,115 --> 00:59:37,574
Just grab it and head out, okay?

996
00:59:37,658 --> 00:59:40,160
-No way! I can't do it!
-Come on, help me out!

997
00:59:40,244 --> 00:59:41,412
I said no. Hey!

998
00:59:46,125 --> 00:59:49,503
SEONGIL STATION

999
00:59:58,512 --> 01:00:02,057
Why'd they have to pick
such a crowded place to meet?

1000
01:00:03,267 --> 01:00:04,560
How am I supposed to know who they are?

1001
01:00:06,895 --> 01:00:08,564
HEATEN PRESSURE RICE COOKER

1002
01:00:09,148 --> 01:00:10,524
I'm sure they'll find me on their own.

1003
01:00:16,697 --> 01:00:17,614
Onion!

1004
01:00:18,157 --> 01:00:19,533
I'LL BE THERE IN 1 MINUTE.
I'M BRINGING A HANDCART.

1005
01:00:23,787 --> 01:00:24,747
I'M BRINGING A HANDCART.

1006
01:00:29,877 --> 01:00:31,003
He's already here.

1007
01:00:39,762 --> 01:00:41,305
Jeez.

1008
01:00:44,975 --> 01:00:46,643
You're here from Onion, right?

1009
01:00:46,727 --> 01:00:47,728
What?

1010
01:00:47,811 --> 01:00:49,897
Oh, that's right. Onion.

1011
01:00:49,980 --> 01:00:51,440
-Is this it?
-Yes.

1012
01:00:58,364 --> 01:00:59,365
Oh…

1013
01:01:15,214 --> 01:01:17,299
I just sent you 320,000 won
through Onion Pay.

1014
01:01:17,925 --> 01:01:19,843
-Excuse me?
-Don't you use Onion Pay?

1015
01:01:20,344 --> 01:01:22,971
-Check your app.
-Oh, I see.

1016
01:01:23,055 --> 01:01:23,931
MELOMASTER: 320,000 WON RECEIVED

1017
01:01:24,515 --> 01:01:26,392
-So this is how you use it.
-And here.

1018
01:01:30,104 --> 01:01:31,355
I'm a fan of Lim Hyeon-jun.

1019
01:01:33,232 --> 01:01:34,608
Oh, thank you.

1020
01:01:34,691 --> 01:01:36,110
I have a whole box at home.

1021
01:01:37,611 --> 01:01:38,570
Have a good night.

1022
01:01:42,950 --> 01:01:43,992
Excuse me.

1023
01:01:50,457 --> 01:01:51,333
Do you like…

1024
01:01:52,793 --> 01:01:53,627
Lim Hyeon-jun?

1025
01:01:54,211 --> 01:01:55,671
Yes, I do.

1026
01:02:48,140 --> 01:02:49,850
It's the first time in my life.

